                <div class="call-and-response">
                    <h3 class="call-and-response__call-title">Question:</h3>
                    <p class="call-and-response__call-body">Is this just UI, or does it cover UX as well?”</p>
                    <div class="orange-arrow"></div>
                    <h3 class="call-and-response__response-title">Answer:</h3>
                    <div class="call-and-response__response-body">
                        <p>Short: it’s about UI, but tangentially cover UX as well.</p>
                        <p>Long: UX (“how it works”) and UI (“how it looks”) are sister disciplines.  It’s hard to separate them.  The aim of this course is to help you make things that look great, but there’s zero point in doing that if usability is zilch.</p>
                        <p>Therefore: I reference topics and ideas from UX constantly in this course, but Learn UI Design is certainly not <em>about</em> them.</p>
